-- The International Olympic Committee said that they will award the Olympic Order to balloonists Bertrand Piccard and Brian Jones who are the first to circumnavigate the world in a balloon. Piccard of Switzerland and Briton Jones joined the first man on the moon, American astronaut Neil Armstrong, and other aeronautical legends such as Charles Lindbergh as recipients of the higly-valued award.
-- A Swiss-Belgian team took off from a lake-side mountain in the Swiss Alps in the latest bid to balloon non-stop around the world.
